"title": "7741: missionaries, task of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7741",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God commits various tasks to his servants. A principal task of those sent by God is to take the good news of the gospel to those who have not heard it, and so to be a means through which others come to faith.</p>\n<h2>The need for missionaries</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:14-Rom10:15\">ROM 10:14–10:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:7\">ISA 52:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:37-Matt9:38\">MAT 9:37–9:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:2\">LUK 10:2</a></p>\n<h2>The work of missionaries</h2>\n<h3>Proclaiming good news</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1-Isa61:2\">ISA 61:1–61:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:18-Luke4:19\">LUK 4:18–4:19</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:43\">LUK 4:43</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:23\">MAT 4:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:35\">MAT 9:35</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:20\">ACT 11:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:42\">ACT 5:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:12\">ACT 8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:25\">ACT 8:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:6-Acts14:7\">ACT 14:6–14:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:16\">ROM 15:16</a></p>\n<h3>Calling people to turn to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:20\">ACT 26:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:6-2Chr30:9\">2CH 30:6–30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:4\">MRK 1:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:3\">LUK 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:19-2Cor5:20\">2CO 5:19–5:20</a></p>\n<h3>Announcing judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:4\">JON 3:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:30-Jer25:31\">JER 25:30–25:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer26:12-Jer26:13\">JER 26:12–26:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek21:2-Ezek21:3\">EZK 21:2–21:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:42\">ACT 10:42</a></p>\n<h3>Teaching and baptising new believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:19–28:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:41-Acts2:42\">ACT 2:41–2:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:12-Acts8:13\">ACT 8:12–8:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:17\">1CO 4:17</a></p>\n<h3>Taking the message further afield</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:15-2Cor10:16\">2CO 10:15–10:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:18-Rom15:20\">ROM 15:18–15:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:28\">ROM 15:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:14\">MAT 24:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:47\">LUK 24:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:9-Acts16:10\">ACT 16:9–16:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:11\">ACT 23:11</a></p>\n<h3>Strengthening newly established churches</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:23\">ACT 18:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:14-Acts8:17\">ACT 8:14–8:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:21-Acts14:23\">ACT 14:21–14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:36-Acts15:41\">ACT 15:36–15:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:4-Acts16:5\">ACT 16:4–16:5</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of other specific assignments</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:10\">EXO 3:10</a> <em>Moses is sent by God to Pharoah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:3\">JOS 22:3</a> <em>The eastern tribes complete their mission to help the others take possession of Canaan</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:14\">JDG 6:14</a> <em>Gideon is sent by God against the Midianites</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:18-1Sam15:20\">1SA 15:18–15:20</a> <em>Saul is given the task of destroying the Amalekites</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:1\">1SA 16:1</a> <em>Samuel is sent by God to anoint David as king</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:15\">ISA 48:15</a> <em>Cyrus is appointed to bring deliverance from Babylon.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:30\">ACT 11:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:25\">ACT 12:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:22\">EPH 6:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:7-Col4:8\">COL 4:7–4:8</a></p>",
